title: "tests/unit is at exactly 120/120 spec files: zero headroom before Gates(static) fails; consolidation candidates identified"
description: "ls tests/unit/*.spec.ts = 120, and static-quality-gate.mjs --max-files-per-dir defaults to 120, so the NEXT spec file added to tests/unit/ breaks CI Gates(static). Relates pm-wc0d (adds a contract test for the cap) but this is the remediation side: free headroom by consolidating duplicated coverage or moving specs into the existing tests/unit/commands/ + tests/unit/core/ subdirectories (each counted separately, far under cap). Verified consolidation candidate: the author-resolution fallback chain (explicit -> env -> settings -> unknown) is asserted end-to-end in at least 5 places: tests/unit/notes-learnings-command.spec.ts:119, tests/unit/comments-command.spec.ts:174, tests/unit/files-docs-command.spec.ts:331 and :824 (files + docs, via shared assertAuthorResolution). The chain could be unit-tested once against the core resolver, with command specs keeping only a single wiring assertion each."
type: Chore
